      "title": "Mangakotukutuku College – Teacher Planning & Reflection Toolkit\\n\\nPurpose: Reduce planning/admin time so kaiako can focus on building strong relationships with ākonga. These templates are lightweight, culturally safe, and aligned with NZC/NCEA.\\n\\nHow to use\\n- Copy any template from ./templates into your planning folder each term/week.\\n- Keep cultural safety at the forefront: complete the Cultural Safety Checklist before publishing materials.\\n- Log whānau engagement and reflections weekly; small habits compound.\\n\\nIncluded templates\\n- Weekly Planner\\n- Lesson Plan Template\\n- Unit Plan Template\\n- Reflective Practice Log\\n- Whānau Engagement Log\\n- Cultural Safety Checklist\\n- NCEA Progress Tracker (CSV)\\n- Student Profile Snapshot\\n\\nKaitiaki notes\\n- Any content containing Māori contexts or local iwi references must be flagged for Kaitiaki review.\\n- If unsure, mark for review and proceed with care (he waka eke noa).\\n",
      "relativePath": "resources/toolkits/MCC_Teacher_Planning_Reflection_Toolkit.md",
      "category": "toolkits",
      "sizeBytes": 948,
      "modifiedAt": "2025-08-14T13:40:03.150Z"
    },
    {
